    },
    {
      "id": "s2",
      "start_char": 128,
      "end_char": 207,
      "summary": "Let A be the event of exactly 2 heads, and B be the event of at least one head.",
      "step_type": "claim"
    },
    {
      "id": "s3",
      "start_char": 209,
      "end_char": 297,
      "summary": "Since A implies B (exactly 2 heads means at least one head), A and B is equivalent to A.",
      "step_type": "derivation"
    },
    {
      "id": "s4",
      "start_char": 299,
      "end_char": 326,
      "summary": "Thus, P(A|B) = P(A) / P(B).",
      "step_type": "conclusion"
    },
    {
      "id": "s5",
      "start_char": 328,
      "end_char": 434,
      "summary": "The probability of exactly 2 heads in 4 flips of a fair coin is given by the binomial probability formula:",
      "step_type": "derivation"
    },
    {
      "id": "s6",
      "start_char": 436,
      "end_char": 495,
      "summary": "P(A) = C(4,2) * (0.5)^2 * (0.5)^2 = 6 * 0.25 * 0.25 = 0.375",
      "step_type": "derivation"
    },
    {
      "id": "s7",
      "start_char": 497,
      "end_char": 544,
      "summary": "Or, in fraction form: C(4,2) / 16 = 6/16 = 3/8.",
      "step_type": "derivation"
    },
    {
      "id": "s8",
      "start_char": 546,
      "end_char": 673,
      "summary": "The probability of at least one head is the complement of all tails: P(B) = 1 - P(all tails) = 1 - (0.5)^4 = 1 - 1/16...",
      "step_type": "derivation"
    },
    {
      "id": "s9",
      "start_char": 675,
      "end_char": 744,
      "summary": "Therefore, P(A|B) = (6/16) / (15/16) = (6/16) * (16/15) = 6/15 = 2/5.",
      "step_type": "conclusion"
    },
    {
      "id": "s10",
      "start_char": 746,
      "end_char": 910,
      "summary": "Alternatively, in the conditional sample space with 15 outcomes (all except all tails), there are 6 outcomes with exa...",
      "step_type": "derivation"
    },
    {
      "id": "s11",
      "start_char": 912,
      "end_char": 959,
      "summary": "Both approaches confirm the probability is 2/5.",
      "step_type": "derivation"
    },
